The 67th Republic Day was celebrated here on Tuesday with several government agencies, organisations and institutions organising programmes to hoist the tricolour and conducting cultural programmes.Hoisting the national flag at Nehru Stadium, Hubballi tahsildar H.D. Nagavi called upon the people to adhere to the principles laid out in the Constitution and participate in nation-building activities.Participating in the celebrations, the former Chief Minister Jagadish Shettar stressed the need for fighting against the caste system and the menace of teorrism.Prasad Abbayya, MLA, stressed the need for the strict implementation of Constitutional provisions to ensure that people of all classes and communities had equal opportunities. Pralhad Joshi, MP, the former Minister Basavaraj Horatti, Pradeep Shettar, MLC, and others were present.Earlier, Mr. Nagavi received a guard of honour from the contingents of the police, home guards, NCC cadets, Scouts and Guides, and schoolchildren.At the Idgah Maidan next to Kittur Chennamma Circle, Commissioner of Hubballi-Dharwad Municipal Corporation (HDMC) C.M. Noor Mansoor hoisted the tricolour in the presence of Mayor Ashwini Majjagi, Pralhad Joshi, MP, and several councillors. As a precaution, the police had barricaded the entire maidan and people were frisked before allowing them to enter. The participants subsequently proceeded to HDMC where Mayor Ashwini Majjagi hoisted the tricolour.At Nehru Stadium, where taluk-level celebrations were held, school children enthralled the spectators by their lively performances. The performance by the girl students of Convent High School, Keshwapur with the theme ‘Care for Earth’, in which the need for protecting our environment was highlighted, drew appreciation from the crowd. Students of several other schools also presented dance based on various themes.The death anniversary of freedom fighter Sangolli Rayanna was observed in the city on Sunday, with government officials and several political leaders paying tributes to the freedom fighter by garlanding his statue at Brindavan Circle here.Celebrations were also held at Sunni Dawat-E-Islami and Jamiya Qadriya Nooriya Namul Uloom at its institute campus in Anchatageri near Hubballi.The former minister and president of Anjuman-E-Islam, Jabbar Khan Honnalli hoisted the national flag.Mr Honnalli stressed the need to adhere to the guidelines laid down by the Constitution.